pageContext.claim: “Thank you to General McMaster. Just more Fake News!”
pageContext.analysis: Trump tweeted an old statement by his former national security adviser, made when he worked for Trump, after The Washington Post reported new information about Trump's meeting with Russian officials after he fired FBI director James Comey -- that "he was unconcerned about Moscow’s interference in the 2016 U.S. presidential election because the United States did the same in other countries."
